The Knowledge of RRB NTPC Syllabus is one of the most important pieces of information that every candidate must know who are preparing for the RRB NTPC Exam. The RRB NTPC Recruitment 2022 notification is released for a total of 35281 vacancies like station master, Senior Clerk cum Typist, etc. The candidates who want to start their career in Railways must know all the important subjects and topics. Questions will be asked from subjects like General Awareness, Mathematics, and General Intelligence and Reasoning. Knowing the RRB NTPC Syllabus and RRB NTPC Exam pattern plays an important role in scoring the maximum number of marks.

  • The candidates undergo 4 stages of the selection process, 1st Stage CBT examination, 2nd Stage CBT Examination, Computer Based Aptitude Test/Typing Test, Document Verification.
  • The Typing Test is applicable to the posts like Senior Clerk Cum Typist, Junior Accounts Assistant Cum Typist, 
  • The Syllabus for Stage 1 and Stage 2 is mentioned in this article. Candidates can also refer to the RRB NTPC Preparation, Tips, and Strategy

The candidates should know the syllabus of the Stage CBT examination and 2nd Stage CBT Examination. Get the complete details regarding the RRB NTPC Syllabus 2022 from this article.

Computer-Based Aptitude Test (Only for Candidates who Opted the post-Traffic Assistant and Station Master)

The candidates who applied for the post of Traffic assistant and station master will have Computer Based Aptitude Test. The candidates have shortlisted 8 times the vacancies of the category. The candidates are shortlisted for CBAT on the basis of marks obtained in the 2nd Stage of the CBT Exam. The candidates scoring at least 70% of marks in the 2nd Stage and 30% of marks in the CLAT examination will be considered in the merit list.

RRB NTPC Junior Translator Free Mock Test

Typing Skill Test (TST) for RRB NTPC Exam 

The typing skill test is conducted for: 

  • Senior Clerk Cum Typist
  • Senior Time Keeper 
  • Accounts Clerk
  • Junior Time Keeper 
  • Junior Clerk Cum Typist. 

The typing Skill test is Qualifying in nature. In Hindi and the English language. Without using any editing tools.

Medium of Language Typing Speed
English 30 words per minute
Hindi 25 words per minute

RRB NTPC Recruitment - Medical Exam

Candidates who will clear the above stags of the selection process will have to pass the physical fitness test conducted by the Railway Administration to make sure that candidates are medically fit to carry out duties connected to the post opted by them. Visual Acuity Standard is one of the important criteria of medical fitness of railway staff.

Candidates can prepare for the Exam by referring to the RRB NTPC Exam Analysis here!

RRB NTPC Recruitment - Document Verification Stage

Based on the performance of candidates in stage II and Stage II candidates equal to the number of vacancies will be called for the Document Verification round. Once all stages of examinations are conducted board will release the final list of selected candidates.

RRB NTPC Syllabus 2022 FAQs

What is the RRB NTPC Syllabus 2022?
The RRB NTPC is CBT 1, CBT2, mainly comprises of 3 subjects that are Mathematics, General Intelligence, and Reasoning and General Awareness
What are the subjects in RRB NTPC Syllabus for CBT Stage I Examination 2022?
Mathematics, General Awareness, General Intelligence, and Reasoning are the subjects in RRB NTPC 1st Stage Examination 2022.
What are the subjects in RRB NTPC Syllabus for CBT Stage II Examination?
The Total questions asked in RRB NTPC 2nd Stage Exam are 120. The RRB NTPC Exam is conducted for 120 marks. The duration is 90 minutes.
What is the difficulty level of the RRB NTPC Examination?
The difficulty level of the RRB NTPC Examination is Moderate.
Where can I find the RRB NTPC Syllabus 2022?
You can get the RRB NTPC Syllabus from the above article.
